A total of six countries have qualified for the quarter-final stage of the ongoing Copa America 2021. The countries are Brazil, Argentina, Chile, Colombia, Paraguay and Uruguay. Uruguay booked their place in the Copa America quarter-finals on Thursday after beating Bolivia 2-0. Argentina and Chile booked their places in the Copa America quarter-finals last Monday. Argentina top Group A with seven points, while Paraguay is in the second position with six points. Meanwhile, Brazil have already qualified from Group B. The Seleção currently top the group with 9 points. The knockout stage starts with the quarter-finals on July 2 and 3. Messi overtakes Ronaldo to become highest scorer of free kicks